An Act creating the ability of police officers to demand FID, LTC or proof of exempt status.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Massachusetts General Laws Section 129C of Chapter 140 is hereby amended by
2 inserting at the end the following new section:-
3 "(n) Any person who, while not being within the limits of their own property or
4 residence, or such person whose property or residence is under lawful search, and who is not
5 exempt under this section, shall on demand of a police officer or other law enforcement officer,
6 exhibit their license to carry firearms, or their firearm identification card or receipt for fee paid
7 for such card, or proof of exempt status under section 129C. Upon failure to do so such person
8 may be required to surrender to such officer said firearm which shall be taken into custody as
9 under the provisions of section one hundred and twenty-nine D, except that such firearm shall be
10 returned forthwith upon presentation within thirty days of said license to carry firearms, firearm
11 identification card, or proof of exempt status, or receipt for fee paid for such card or license as
12 hereinbefore described. Any person subject to the conditions of this paragraph may, even though
